description.narrative: (USAID West Africa Regional): FY 2017 funds will support the service delivery component of USAID/West Africa's family planning (FP) strategy within USG commitments to the Ouagadougou Partnership and the FP2020 initiative. USAID's goal is to increase access to and use of quality FP services in selected West African countries. FY 2017 activities include: .Strengthening voluntary FP services in West Africa following the high level ECOWAS parliamentarian's declaration on health financing and harnessing the demographic dividend in West Africa, maximizing legacy outputs and catalyzing implementation and sharing of selected FP high impact practices, thus contributing to OP goals of 2.2 million additional FP users in West Africa by 2020. .This activity meets the President's America First vision through directly asserting U.S. leadership and influence in FP/RH programming and indirectly contributes to harnessing a demographic dividend and improved security in West Africa.
